<title>≠kasin shoots a hyena</title>
<summary>≠kasin follows his dogs to a hyena&apos;s hole. The dogs pull the hyena out and ≠kasin shoots it. He sees a snake under a rock and runs home, where the people accuse him of being angry like the snake and disagreeable at home.</summary><comments>1) p.3468v: the Dutch name for the snake is s<i>wart slang</i>, 2) p.3470v: the family told ≠kasin that he had now met a snake as angry and disagreeable as himself, 3) This story is found in Book IV-1</comments><date>7 November 1873</date><storypages>3465-3471</storypages><category>History (personal)</category><author>≠kasin (Klaas Katkop) (IV)</author><keyword><kw>≠kasin</kw><subkw>his behaviour</subkw></keyword>
